# Offer of Internship — AI Intern (Legal-marked)
Date: [Offer Date]

Dear Candidate,

We are pleased to offer you a fixed-term internship with Omninuera for the position of AI Intern under the terms set out below. This document is an HR draft for review and is intended to be provided to the candidate; it will be sent to Legal for review prior to finalization.

Position and Term
- Position: AI Intern.
- Duration: 3 months (fixed-term internship).
- Start Date: [Start Date].
- Reporting to: [Manager Name], [Title].

Work Arrangement and Location
- Work arrangement: Remote-first (candidate is expected to work remotely unless otherwise required).
- Candidate city (for record): Bengaluru.
- Location clause: This internship is remote-first. Candidate will be based in Bengaluru and must comply with applicable local laws. The Company may require you to attend the Company premises in Bengaluru on reasonable notice.

Stipend and Payment
- Stipend: INR 10,000 per month.
- Payment schedule: The stipend will be paid monthly in arrears and will be disbursed within the first week of the following month by bank transfer. The stipend stated is subject to all applicable statutory deductions and withholdings (including but not limited to income-tax/TDS, Professional Tax, EPF or ESI contributions) only where required by law. The Company will determine the applicability of such deductions in accordance with applicable statutes and notify the Candidate. The stipend will be pro‑rated for any partial month of service.

Internship Status
- Nature of engagement and training focus: This engagement is a fixed-term, training-oriented internship with defined learning objectives and supervision. It is not intended to create a permanent employer-employee relationship for all purposes. The internship duties are limited to training, project work and supervised tasks set out by the reporting manager; you will not be treated as a regular full-time employee for benefit eligibility except as expressly stated in writing. Whether statutory employment laws (including the Minimum Wages Act, EPF and ESI laws) apply is a question of law and fact; where required by statute, the Company will comply with such laws and make any applicable contributions or deductions.

Confidentiality
- During the internship and thereafter, the Candidate must maintain the confidentiality of Omninuera’s confidential and proprietary information and may not disclose such information to any third party except as authorized in writing by Omninuera. Confidential information includes, but is not limited to, technical data, business plans, product roadmaps, customer information, source code, models, training data, and other proprietary materials. You will be required to sign the Company’s standard Confidentiality Agreement as a condition of joining.

Intellectual Property
- Intellectual Property and confidentiality:
  (a) Assignment of IP: All inventions, discoveries, developments, designs, code, machine learning models, documentation and other work product (collectively, 'Company IP') that you create, solely or jointly, during the period of your engagement and within the scope of assigned tasks or using Company resources, shall be the sole and exclusive property of Omninuera. You hereby irrevocably assign, and agree to assign, to Omninuera all right, title and interest in such Company IP and shall execute any documents and take all actions reasonably requested by the Company to vest and perfect those rights.
  (b) Confidentiality: You shall keep confidential and not disclose Company proprietary information and trade secrets during and after the internship for a period of two (2) years (or such longer period as may be required by law or by written agreement) except where disclosure is required by law. Exceptions: information that is or becomes public through no fault of yours or that you receive lawfully from a third party without confidentiality obligations.
  (c) Execution of documents: As a condition to joining, you will execute the Company’s standard Confidentiality and IP Assignment Agreement and any related onboarding documents. Failure to sign such documents may result in withdrawal of the offer.

Termination and Notice
- Termination for convenience: Either party may terminate this internship for convenience by providing seven (7) calendar days’ written notice to the other party.
- Termination for cause: Omninuera may terminate the internship immediately for material breach of this offer, misconduct, violation of company policies, or other serious grounds. In the event of termination, stipend will be pro-rated to the last day worked and paid in accordance with the payment schedule, subject to applicable deductions.
- Termination and statutory rights: In addition to the termination rights set out above, termination and other employment-rights consequences will be subject to applicable statutory obligations if you are found to be an employee under any applicable law.
- Any early termination will be handled in accordance with Omninuera’s standard exit procedures.

Compliance with Company Policies
- The Candidate must comply with Omninuera’s policies and procedures, including those relating to confidentiality, information security, acceptable use, and workplace conduct. Omninuera may update its policies from time to time.
- POSH policy and internal complaints committee (ICC): Omninuera’s policy on prevention of sexual harassment applies to all personnel including interns. The POSH policy is available at [insert POSH policy URL]. You may raise complaints with the Internal Complaints Committee (ICC) at [ICC contact email and phone].

Background Verification
- This offer is conditional on satisfactory background verification (education, employment history, and any other checks deemed appropriate by Omninuera) and your signed consent to the Background Verification process set out in Annexure A. Omninuera reserves the right to withdraw the offer if verification is unsatisfactory.

Tax and Deductions
- Taxation and statutory deductions: The stipend shall be subject to income tax in accordance with the Income-tax Act, 1961. The Company will deduct tax at source as required by law based on the characterization of the stipend and applicable thresholds. You are responsible for your personal tax filings and liabilities; the Company will provide necessary tax certificates where applicable.
- Social security and professional tax: Where applicable under the Employees’ Provident Fund & Miscellaneous Provisions Act, 1952, Employees’ State Insurance Act, 1948, or Karnataka professional tax laws (or any successor statutes), the Company will register and/or make contributions and deductions as required by law. Applicability depends on statutory criteria (including establishment coverage and employee classification). The Company will inform the Candidate of any statutory contributions that are to be made from the stipend or by the Company.

No Guarantee of Employment
- Completion of the internship does not guarantee an offer of employment. Any offer of employment following the internship will be subject to a separate agreement.

Acceptance Instructions
To accept this offer, please sign and return a scanned copy of this letter or send an email confirmation to HR at [HR Email Address] by no later than seven (7) calendar days from the date of this offer ([Acceptance Deadline: date to be inserted by HR]). Acceptance should include the Candidate’s printed name and signature and confirmation of the Start Date.

Condition precedent to joining
- This offer is subject to (i) satisfactory background verification; (ii) your execution of the Company’s standard onboarding documents (including confidentiality and IP assignment and background-consent forms); and (iii) the Company’s assessment of statutory applicability. The Company will retain a copy of executed consents and verification results for compliance purposes.

